```css
button {
  background-color: #008040;
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
}
```

**Explanation:**

* `background-color`: Sets the background color of the button to a bright green color.
* `color`: Sets the text color to white.
* `padding`: Adds padding to the button for visual appeal.
* `border`: Removes the default border of the button.
* `border-radius`: Adds rounded corners to the button.

**Usage:**

To use the CSS code, simply add it to the `<button>` element in your HTML document.

```html
<button>My Button</button>
```

**Additional Notes:**

* You can adjust the color values in the `background-color` and `color` properties to create different color combinations.
* You can also customize the padding, border-radius, and other styling properties to achieve different visual effects.

